Traffic Light Control System with Pedestrian Switch (Arduino)

This project implements a simple traffic light controller using an Arduino. The system simulates a real-world traffic signal with Red, Yellow, and Green LEDs for vehicles, along with a pedestrian push button that allows pedestrians to safely request a crossing.

When the pedestrian button is pressed, the controller completes the current traffic cycle, safely stops vehicle traffic by turning the vehicle light red, and provides a designated crossing period before returning to normal operation.

Features
Simulates a standard traffic light sequence.
Pedestrian crossing request using a push button.
Safe transition from vehicle green to pedestrian crossing.
Prevents abrupt signal changes.
Demonstrates digital input and output handling in Arduino.
Easily expandable to include pedestrian LEDs, buzzers, or countdown timers.
