Working Principle
The traffic signal follows a normal sequence:
Green → Yellow → Red → Green
During normal operation, the Arduino continuously checks the pedestrian push button.
When the button is pressed:
A pedestrian crossing request is registered.
The current traffic phase is allowed to finish safely.
The vehicle signal changes to Red.
Pedestrians are given sufficient time to cross.
After the crossing interval, the system resumes the normal traffic light cycle.
